we are gievn an inlut array of size n containing n number . We have to sort this array in incremental order with out using the sort function.

Counting sort: When there are a small set of number in a array.
We can first compute the maximum and then use this maximum as array size to count the occurrences of all the numbers in the range 0 to maximum.
once we have to count array with counts of all the number occurrences, we can build the sorted array.

code:

class solution{
    public void sortColors(int[] nums)
    {

    int max = nums[0];

    for(int i : nums)
    {
     max = Math.max(i, max);
     }

     int [] arr = new int[max + 1];
     Arrays.fill(arr, 0);

     for(int i: nums)
     {
      arr[i]++;
      }

      int index =0;

      for(int i = 0; i < arr.count; i++)
      {

        while( arr[i)>0)
        {
         nums[index] = i;
         arr[i]--;
         index++;
         }

        }

        }
    }
